//This file will read the side info of mp3 Frames and save the data we need for decoding and playing the file. It also contains some helper functions for reading the header and applying the tables to get real values for bitrate and samplerate. The main function in this file is 'getMP3SideInfo' which will read the side info of a mp3 frame and save the data into a struct. You can use this data later for decoding and playing the file. The side info is different for mono and stereo files, so we will have to check the number of channels in the header to know how to read the side info.